    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-11T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="768"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d768">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/2048</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-11T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 11, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6247. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 434. Replying Embassy’s 5695, November 3, 6 p.m., your 559.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d768fn1">Not printed.</note> Your attention is called to the
                    official publication of the capture of 250,000 horses in Italy. If there should
                    be further need of animals for Army, cannot these be employed and save
                    exportation of ammonium sulphate to Spain in exchange for mules? Is it <pb
                        facs="0881" n="1715" xml:id="pg_1715"/> possible that with the conclusion of
                    an armistice this purchase of mules would not need to be consummated since we
                    are very anxious to save the ammonium sulphate? Offer them flour.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
